item.title: About
item.description: The California Weekly Pulse site was created and is maintained by the Stanford Data Lab. If you have any feedback, comments, or suggestions for improvements to this site, please email us.

item.title: Alameda County
item.description: Food insecurity Unemployment Food insecurity The estimates of food insecurity in Alameda County are based upon a model. The model uses the overall rate of food insecurity for the state, which is updated every week, and the unemployment rate for each county, which is updated every month. The unemployment data for a month comes out later than the food insecurity data. For months where unemployment data is not yet available, the model uses the latest month for which data is available.

item.title: California
item.description: Overview Food insecurity Unemployment Overview The data on this site is derived from the U.S. Census Bureau Household Pulse Survey (HPS) and the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics Local Area Unemployment Statistics (LAUS). New HPS data is released once a week, and new LAUS data is released once a month. The most recent data used for this report are: Household Pulse Survey: May 28 - June 2 Local Area Unemployment Statistics: April The HPS releases data in two stages.
